The Proteas have won the toss and elected to bat first against India in their Cricket World Cup encounter at the Rose Bowl in Southampton on Wednesday. The Proteas have endured a wretched start to the tournament, losing to hosts England by 104 runs then slipping to a 21-run loss to Bangladesh on Sunday. This will be India's opening game of their World Cup campaign. Hashim Amla returns for the India clash after missing the second match following a hit on the head during the tournament opener against England. Tabraiz Shamsi is in for the injured Lungi Ngidi. Meanwhile, Dale Steyn and Ngidi are the two players unavailable - Steyn has been ruled out of the squad while Ngidi is expected to miss two games. Teams: South Africa Quinton de Kock (wicketkeeper), Hashim Amla, Faf du Plessis (captain), Rassie van der Dussen, David Miller, JP Duminy, Andile Phehlukwayo, Chris Morris, Kagiso Rabada, Imran Tahir, Tabraiz Shamsi India Rohit Sharma, Shikhar Dhawan, Virat Kohli (captain), KL Rahul, Kedar Jadhav, MS Dhoni (wicketkeeper), Hardik Pandya, Bhuvneshwar Kumar, Kuldeep Yadav, Yuzvendra Chahal, Jasprit Bumrah  https://www.sport24.co.za/Cricket/CricketWorldCup2019/proteas-win-toss-bat-first-against-india-20190605